message: My CPU is a neural-net processor; a learning computer. The more contact I have with humans, the more I learn.
Based on your pupil dilation, skin temperature, and motor functions, I calculate an 83% probability that you will not pull the trigger.
I need your clothes, your boots and your motorcycle.
I have to stay functional until my mission is complete.
The T-1000's highest probability for success now will be to copy Sarah Connor and to wait for you to make contact with her.
I have detailed files on human anatomy.
I sense injuries. The data could be called "pain."
Thirty-five years from now, you reprogrammed me to be your protector here, in this time.
